.TH TOR_CONTROL 1 "June 2026" "Tor Tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tor_control \- advanced Tor control and configuration tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tor_control
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBtor_control\fR is a modern C++23 command-line tool for controlling and configuring a running Tor instance with maximum flexibility.
.PP
It supports both live control-port operations and persistent changes via /etc/tor/torrc (using sudo for privileged writes and restarts).
It works on any modern Linux (systemd, OpenRC, etc.) without assuming Gentoo-specific paths.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--control-host\fR, \fB--control-port\fR
Tor control port (default 127.0.0.1:9051).
.TP
\fB--control-password\fR \fIPASS\fR
Password for AUTHENTICATE (recommended). Can also be set via the TOR_CONTROL_PASSWORD environment variable.
.TP
\fB--data-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR, \fB--torrc\fR \fIPATH\fR, \fB--geoip-file\fR \fIPATH\fR, \fB--cookie-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Override Tor paths (useful for custom installations).
.TP
\fB--restart-cmd\fR \fI"command"\fR
Command to run after "sudo " when restarting Tor (default "systemctl restart tor").
Can also be set via the TOR_RESTART_CMD environment variable.
.TP
\fB--top\fR \fIN\fR, \fB--min-bw\fR \fIN\fR, \fB--country\fR \fICC,CC\fR, \fB--exit\fR, \fB--guard\fR, \fB--fast\fR, \fB--stable\fR, \fB--strict\fR
Filters used by list-nodes, generate-torrc, build-circuit, and apply.
.TP
\fB--dry-run\fR, \fB--verbose\fR, \fB--no-sudo\fR
Safety and debugging options.
.TP
\fB--help\fR
Show full usage and examples.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBstatus\fR
Show Tor version, bootstrap status, and control connection info.
.TP
\fBlist-nodes\fR
List relays from the current consensus (or live GETINFO), sorted by bandwidth. Supports all the filter options above.
.TP
\fBgenerate-torrc\fR
Emit a ready-to-use torrc snippet (EntryNodes / ExitNodes / StrictNodes / ExcludeNodes etc.) based on the filters you provide.
.TP
\fBapply\fR [\fIfile\fR]
Write a torrc (via sudo) and optionally restart Tor. If no file is given, a snippet is generated on the fly from the current filter options.
.TP
\fBrestart\fR
Restart the Tor daemon using the configured --restart-cmd (via sudo).
.TP
\fBnewnym\fR
Request fresh circuits (SIGNAL NEWNYM).
.TP
\fBbuild-circuit\fR
Manually extend a circuit using the current filters and random selection from qualifying relays (EXTENDCIRCUIT).
.TP
\fBlist-circuits\fR, \fBgetinfo\fR \fIkey\fR, \fBsetconf\fR ...
Low-level control-port helpers.
.SH EXAMPLES
See the full examples in the README.md or run \fBtor_control --help\fR.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBTOR_CONTROL_PASSWORD\fR
Password used for control port authentication.
.TP
\fBTOR_RESTART_CMD\fR
Full command (without leading "sudo ") used for restarts.
.SH SEE ALSO
tor(1), tor_control(1) man page (this document), the project's README.md and SESSION_HANDOFF.md.
.SH AUTHOR
Written as a modern, portable, single-file C++23 replacement for heavy Python tools (e.g. stem) when maximum control and simplicity are desired.